ukfk - a process killer for commands running under current connected session
useful for when you have a terminal with a stuck command, but can open a new shell

setup:
  Dependencies:
    procps-ng
      check with: w -s|head -n 2|tail -n 1
      you're looking for: USER, TTY, FROM, IDLE, WHAT
      if this isn't lined up, this program wont work

    ExtUtils::MakeMaker;
        perl-ExtUtils-MakeMaker or maybe the perl-devel package

  install:
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

  usage:
    unfk

